name: Luhur Besikalung Temple
address: Babahan, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1: What a truly magical place. The stone artwork is amazing, and the forest garden adds to the magic.
review 3: Loved the experience. You can see some of the rituals in here. Beatiful to see.
review 4: Hindu temple in the middle of the rice fields terrasse. When I went there it was empty, itâ€™s an authentic place to worship.
review 5: This place is good place even though this place bit hidden from the city but this place could be great start point for having trekking site in jati luwih rice terrace

name: Tridatu waroeng bamboo
address: Banjar Dinas Utu, Babahan, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1: Refreshing view with good local food and very friendly owner. The grilled chicken was especially tasty. Take a stroll after the meal and enjoy the swing and wonderful landscape the place offers!
review 2: It was the best food that we had in Bali. What a special experience!!! The owners is extremely welcoming and friendly. This was an experience on its own great food and good company. The fried rice and chicken dish is very very good. Strongly recommend the red rice tea. I just love this special place. Everyone needs to visit here!!!
review 3: Beautifull views and delicious nasi and mie goreng! Such a nice
review 4:
The best food we had in Bali. The owner and his wife are amazing, we felt at home and we had an insight of the Bali culture. They speak amazing English so you can have a chat to find out more about their life and their culture.
100% worth the detour, for the food, the atmosphere and the view. Youâ€™re in the middle of rice fields overlooking three mountains.
If we ever come back to Bali, visiting will be a must!
review 5:
100% recommended!
We came at 7pm and Arta and his wife were already about to leave due to no guests. They were so kind to reopen the restaurant for us and made us one of the most delicious dinners we had in Bali so far. I could order any meal from the menu and they would make a vegetarian variation for me, which I really appreciated.
Also in general they both were super nice and friendly and Arta even spoke German with us, which was pretty surprising!

name: Magical Breeze Cabin
address: Banjar utu, Babahan, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Arta and his family were the best hosts! We will be back and tell all our friends about it. Kia Ora from New Zealand my friend.
review 2: The surroundings is so much better than the pictures. The host Arta is very helpful and easy to communicate with, the room is also equipped with everything you need. There is no air conditioning but itâ€™s not needed as the area is refreshly cold, also walking distance to a nice waterfall and a restaurant next door.
review 3: Great place, beautiful view of the rice fields, at night you can hear cicadas and see fireflies, 10 minutes from the accommodation there is a waterfall where nobody comes (almost like a private waterfall), 12 minutes into town there are local hot springs under the bridge. Very nice hosts!
review 4: Had such a special time here. Arta is an absolute legend and very accommodating. There is so much surrounding beauty in these parts. Definitely do some waterfalls and bird watching here. Jutiluwih is great too ðŸŒ¾
review 5:
I really enjoyed the serenity of the atmosphere around the cabin with my partner.. we really enjoyed the natural beauty around the cabin area.. starting from waterfalls, rice fields, very friendly locals... and amazing evenings...
i am very very happy to find a place like this cabin... thank you and  if I could give more than 5 Stars I will give them 100 stars lovely

name: Warung samboga besikalung
address: J4FR+FRW, Jatiluwih, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1:
We wanna order coconut but owner said no, then we order dragon fruit and orange juice, when I pay the bill, dragon fruit cost 40K, fresh juice 35K which normally should be 20K and 15K, after payment I see why they did not sell coconut, because coconut was sold only 20K inside Jatiluwih rice terrace, they cannot sell it double price outside the rice terrace.
Recommend to have coconut inside rice terrace.
review 2:
My visit was back in
2019 October. Been had lunch here 3 days in row !! The food was amazing, the owner was generous and kind. She gave us, desert, entre, and cacao fruit for our way back as complimentary. My partner wanted to try eel, and they prepared for us the next day. And he loved it!!
I totally recommended if you visit jatiluwih. Located not far from Pura Besi Kalung, but if you are from entrance of rice fields, you need to walk until almost the end of the rice fields.
The view was calming, quiet, and you can enjoy it for yourself.
review 3: Beautiful place in the middle of the rice fields. Lovely local people. Cheap prices. Get some rest of the long walk. Delicious food.
review 4:
They are really nice but I am sorry, I donâ€™t like how they do the business.
We didnâ€™t ask chips but they give us with the juice, we thought it was complimentary but they charge it 20k in the bill.
We ordered curry but it was not a curry that they served, its more like stir fried vegetables with soup, and they charge 70k for every plate.
Fried rice came with only rice and a small amount of eggs as a topping. No veggies or even chicken. They charge 45k for every plates.
For a small warung and the food that you get, the price is expensive and tasteless.

The good thing is only the view.
review 5: the food is delicious, the service is very good and friendly, the food prices are also very affordable. The place is beautiful, surrounded by views of green rice fields.

name: The Kumpi
address: J49W+4G8, Banjar Utu, Babahan, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia

name: Warung Mina Nugraha
address: Jl.Subak Kedamean, Jatiluwih, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1: After a long hike this place was a paradise in the middle of rice fields. Very tasty food, hospitable family, a puppy and a black rooster! Definitely recommend!
review 2: For such outstanding places google should add 6-star rating. Right after crossing treshold of this restaurat we were welcomed as family, food was absolutly amazing, we ate here one of the best dinner in Bali. I can't say any bad word! Totally worth to taking 2 minutes of trial for such wonderful expiriences in the middle od ricefields.
review 3: I highly recommend this place. Food was excellent, we ate here one of the best Nasi Goreng. Stuff was amazing too, very friendly and helpfull. The place is located far from crowded main road where most restaurants are placed (and they are much expensive) and in the middle of the rice fields, so you will have calm meal here.
review 4: I accidentally stumbled upon Warung Mina Nugraha while trekking alone. I met the most friendly people, had some great fish and stayed for a few cup of teas. Lovely people!
